    <title>Tutor</title>
    <page>
        <question id="q1">
            <body>What is the approximate test statistic for p-hat = 0.74? <input_ref input="A"
                /></body>
            <numeric id="A"/>
            <part>
                <response input="A" match="[0.958, 1.042]" score="10">
                    <feedback>Correct. The test statistic is about 1, since p-hat = 0.74 is 0.10 above p<sub>0</sub> = 0.64 and 0.10 is 
                        is 1 standard deviation.</feedback>
                </response>
                <response input="A" match="*">
                    <feedback>Incorrect. The test statistic is the number of standard deviations that p-hat = 0.74 is above p<sub>0</sub> = 0.64.</feedback>
                </response>
                <hint>The test statistic is the number of standard deviations
                    p-hat = 0.74 is from p<sub>0</sub> = 0.64.</hint>
                <hint>p-hat = 0.74 is 0.10 above p<sub>0</sub> = 0.64.</hint>
                <hint>p-hat is 1 standard deviation above p<sub>0</sub>.</hint>
                <hint>The test statistic is approximately 1.</hint>
            </part>
        </question>
    </page>
